#Ebola: +2 cases, in Mbandaka (big city, bad news). 3 deaths.
Totals to date: 62 cases & 27 deaths.
This is already the 12th largest Ebola outbreak ever. West Africa & North Kivu have changed our views on how big outbreaks can get but historically most involve 3-5 dozen cases.]

- Mon 20 Jul 2020
[CIDRAP (Center for Infectious Disease Research and Policy) abridged, edited]
https://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2020/07/news-scan-jul-20-2020

Ebola infects 3 more in the DRC, lifting cases to 60 [62 cases as of 22 Jul 2020]

At a media briefing today [20 Jul 2020], Mike Ryan, MD, who directs the WHO's health emergencies program, said the outbreak is worrying, given the dispersed nature of the outbreak, which is spread across 21 health areas in 7 health zones. Also, he said 9 people with confirmed infections are still in the community, a factor known to raise the risk of further transmission.

Investigations so far suggest that about 1 in 3 cases are linked to attending funeral, also a known transmission risk. Others have been linked to exposure in healthcare settings and among family members.

Ibrahima Soce Fall, MD, the WHO's assistant director-general for emergency response, said there are teams on the ground and the response is still scaling up, with participation by a range of partners, which is challenging in the context of the COVID-19 pandemic.

